CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper January 7, 1956, pg. C11, reads: "Woods Run Star Staff - Members of the Woods Run Star newspaper staff of the Woods Run Settlement recently toured the Courier plant.  During the tour, they talked with Courier employes [employees] and asked many questions.  Left to right, seated, Ralph E. Koger, Courier assistant city editor; Mrs. Dolores Redwood, Courier stenographer, who acted as guide; Bernie Smith, circulation manager of the Star; reporters Nancy Macon, Marvin Scott and 'Johnny' White; Janice Johnson, feature editor; Minnie Hallamon, society editor; Francine White, editor; 'Libby' Smith, sports editor, and George Sherbon, student in the School of Journalism, Duquesne University, and adult advisor of the Star, and Mrs. Willa Mae Rice, Courier reporter. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Children from Woods Run Star newspaper visiting Pittsburgh Courier offices and staff, including from left: Ralph E. Koger, Dolores Redwood, Bernie Smith, Nancy Macon, Marvin Scott, Johnny White, Janice Johnson, Minnie Hallamon, Francine White, Libby Smith, sports editor, George Sherbon, and Willa Mae Rice
